pullsbody:
Bumps [acorn](https://github.com/acornjs/acorn) from 6.2.1 to 6.4.1.
Commits
  • 9a2e9b6 Mark version 6.4.1
  • 90a9548 More rigorously check surrogate pairs in regexp validator
  • df0cf1a Mark version 6.4.0
  • 5303412 Also export Parser via Parser.acorn
  • efe273e give token types and etc to plugins
  • ac6decb Mark version 6.3.0
  • 7e9817d Allow sourceType: module even with ecmaVersion < 6
  • e2b8cc0 Fix broken parsing of new expressions when allowReserved=="never"
  • 1555c52 Update acorn.d.ts
  • See full diff in compare view

[![Dependabot compatibility score](https://dependabot-badges.githubapp.com/badges/compatibility_score?dependency-name=acorn&package-manager=npm_and_yarn&previous-version=6.2.1&new-version=6.4.1)](https://help.github.com/articles/configuring-automated-security-fixes) Dependabot will resolve any conflicts with this PR as long as you don't alter it yourself. You can achieve the same result by closing it manually - `@dependabot ignore this major version` will close this PR and stop Dependabot creating any more for this major version (unless you reopen the PR or upgrade to it yourself) - `@dependabot ignore this minor version` will close this PR and stop Dependabot creating any more for this minor version (unless you reopen the PR or upgrade to it yourself) - `@dependabot ignore this dependency` will close this PR and stop Dependabot creating any more for this dependency (unless you reopen the PR or upgrade to it yourself) - `@dependabot use these labels` will set the current labels as the default for future PRs for this repo and language - `@dependabot use these reviewers` will set the current reviewers as the default for future PRs for this repo and language - `@dependabot use these assignees` will set the current assignees as the default for future PRs for this repo and language - `@dependabot use this milestone` will set the current milestone as the default for future PRs for this repo and language You can disable automated security fix PRs for this repo from the [Security Alerts page](https://github.com/mozilla/activate.mozilla.community/network/alerts).

pulltitle: Add Newsletter languages again + make country optional (fixes #331)
pullsbody:
You can find this at http://activate-test.michaelkohler.info/. You might need to force reload to see the change.

Please test the following scenarios:
* Nothing selected
* German selected
* German selected - some Country selected
* and then point 2 and 3 for all languages

Question: Should we display the languages in their native language? For now it would be English only (and non localizeable).

Note: the form on /newsletter is exactly the same as would be shown when there is no campaign, so no need to test that scenario additionally

pulltitle: Improvement, updating and addition of new translations for PT-BR
pullsbody:
Hello Activate team,

I have worked today **updating, improving and adding new translations**, are not complete yet, but we will work collaboratively among volunteers and then we'll send new translations ASAP.

**Some observations are important:**

- I not find any files to add translations of the activities (summary, type of activity, name and time) located in the home page and in the footer.
- Our language is derived from Portuguese from Portugal, but our Portuguese is Brazilian, so the correct one is use PT-BR. It is not good practice to use PT for Brazilian Portuguese, because our community in Portugal may want to translate this project in the future and they will want to use PT in the "lang".
- Finally, I believe that some updates are need in the FAQ page.

Cheers 👍 
Geraldo Barros
pull_commit_message: Improvement, updating and addition of new translations for PT-BR

pulltitle: List activities on frontpage + nicer activity overview
pullsbody:
Changelog:
* We removed the categories
* Activities are now shown on the frontpage for easy access
* There is a slider at the bottom of the frontpage to give you tips on where to start
* Activities have a tag on the bottom left of the box to indicate what skill set they belong to (for now "Programming", "Participation" and "Testing")
* Those tags are also indicated by the border color of the box
* Activities now have nice pictures to quickly identify them
* The suggested duration of each activity can now be seen without opening it
